postcontent: Please Call 678-718-8067Monday - Friday 8am-3pm.Please read the Item Characteristics for important listing details.This auction is for a used Springfield Armory 1898 Krag in 30-40. This is a fine specimen and would make for a wonderful winter restoration project. The barrel is a full 30 inches with orginal sights. The stock however has been cut to carbine length, or "sporterized" as was very common in yesteryear. Everything works as it should, but the magazine hinge pin is slightly bent. The stock is 30 1/2 inches long and the LOP is 14inches. Inclueded but not pictured is a used steel butt plate with screws and the front barrel band cap and screw. title: For Sale:  BFONG PPSH41
postcontent: Up for sale is a Indianapolis Ordnance PPSH-41 BFONG (Blank Fire Only Non-Gun). This CAN NOT be made to fire live ammunition under any circumstance. Loading or attempting to load live ammunition will result in catastrophic damage to the gun and injury or death. DO NOT attempt to load live ammunition! This is a fully automatic blank fire only gun. It is ATF approved as a non-gun. It fires 9.3 BFONG blanks which can be found at either Atlantic Wall Blanks or Swanson Blanks. It is used for WW2 reenacting but also can be used for many time periods where this weapon was present. It is in good condition and functions the last time I have fired it. It could use a little tuning. (Done with a hex-wrench) But functions very well. As with any and all full auto blank guns, it can sometimes be finicky and require adjusting and tuning depending on weather/temp and the blanks you are using. These are forward firing BFONGs unlike the SSRoom ones which fire backward. There for you can use standard PPSH-41 mags and drums (some fitting with drums may be required). Included is a sling, PPSH41 mag pouch that is missing one of it's wood toggles - an easy fix, and 4 magazines that are in good but military surplus condition. I also have a bag of blanks included...I am unsure how many blanks are in the bag. Approx 250 or more would be my best guess. I may be open to some partial trades. But be warned - I am a bit picky. Perfect for Soviet WW2 Reenacting, Vietnam Era reenacting, or if you do German WW2 - as a captured weapon for the Eastern Front!I am looking to get rid of the whole package for 2000 + shipping and insurance. I take PayPal as a primary form of payment. PP fee will be added into shipping cost. Thanks!
